ed by magic.\n\nOutside an antimagic field or any other effect that suppresses magic, these lungs allow you to breathe normally in any environment (including a vacuum), and you have advantage on saving throws against harmful gases such as those created by a Cloudkill spell, a Stinking Cloud spell, inhaled poisons, and gaseous breath weapons .\n\nAs an action, you can use these lungs to exhale a gust of wind, as if you had cast the Gust of Wind spell (spell save DC 15) with no components. This property of the lungs can\u0027t be used again until the next dawn.\n\nIf your attunement to the lungs ends, your original lungs reappear.","grantedAtLevel":10,"infusion":{"active":false,"attuned":false,"choose":0,"desc":"Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)\n\nThese metallic nodules were created in response to the poisonous gases used on the battlefields of the Last War. When you attune to these lungs, they replace the lungs in your chest, which disappear. The lungs allow you to breathe normally, even in an antimagic field, and their breathing function can\u0027t be suppressed by magic.\n\nOutside an antimagic field or any other effect that suppresses magic, these lungs allow you to breathe normally in any environment (including a vacuum), and you have advantage on saving throws against harmful gases such as those created by a Cloudkill spell, a Stinking Cloud spell, inhaled poisons, and gaseous breath weapons .\n\nAs an action, you can use these lungs to exhale a gust of wind, as if you had cast the Gust of Wind spell (spell save DC 15) with no components. This property of the lungs can\u0027t be used again until the next dawn.\n\nIf your attunement to the lungs ends, your original lungs reappear.","grantedAtLevel":10,"level":0,"name":"Ventilating Lungs (Eberron: Rising from the Last War)"},"maxActive":{"static":0},"name":"Ventilating Lungs (Eberron: Rising from the Last War)"},{"activationRequirement":{},"description":"Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)\n\nWhile you wear these boots, you have a flying speed equal to your walking speed. You can use the boots to fly for up to 4 hours, all at once or in several shorter flights, each one using a minimum of 1 minute from the duration. If you are flying when the duration expires, you descend at a rate of 30 feet per round until you land.\n\nThe boots regain 2 hours of flying capability for every 12 hours they aren\u0027t in use.","grantedAtLevel":10,"infusion":{"active":false,"attuned":false,"choose":0,"desc":"Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)\n\nWhile you wear these boots, you have a flying speed equal to your walking speed. You can use the boots to fly for up to 4 hours, all at once or in several shorter flights, each one using a minimum of 1 minute from the duration. If you are flying when the duration expires, you descend at a rate of 30 feet per round until you land.\n\nThe boots regain 2 hours of flying capability for every 12 hours they aren\u0027t in use.","grantedAtLevel":10,"level":0,"name":"Winged Boots"},"maxActive":{"static":0},"name":"Winged Boots"},{"activationRequirement":{},"description":"Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)\n\nYour Constitution score is 19 while you wear this amulet. It has no effect on you if your Constitution is 19 or higher without it.","grantedAtLevel":14,"infusion":{"active":false,"attuned":false,"choose":0,"desc":"Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)\n\nYour Constitution score is 19 while you wear this amulet. It has no effect on you if your Constitution is 19 or higher without it.","grantedAtLevel":14,"level":0,"name":"Amulet of Health"},"maxActive":{"static":0},"name":"Amulet of Health"},{"activationRequirement":{},"description":"Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunement by a creature missing a hand or an arm)\n\nThis prosthetic appendage was developed by artificers of House Cannith. To attune to this item, you must attach it to your arm at the wrist, elbow, or shoulder, at which point the prosthetic magical