elf, transforming into a bat. While you are in the form of the bat, you retain your Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores. The cloak can\u0027t be used this way again until the next dawn.","grantedAtLevel":14,"level":0,"name":"Cloak of the Bat"},"maxActive":{"static":0},"name":"Cloak of the Bat"},{"activationRequirement":{},"description":"Wondrous item, rare\n\nYou can use an action to place these shackles on an incapacitated creature. The shackles adjust to fit a creature of Small to Large size. In addition to serving as mundane manacles, the shackles prevent a creature bound by them from using any method of extradimensional movement, including teleportation or travel to a different plane of existence. They don\u0027t prevent the creature from passing-through an interdimensional portal.\n\nYou and any creature you designate when you use the shackles can use an action to remove them. Once every 30 days, the bound creature can make a DC 30 Strength (Athletics) check. On a success, the creature breaks free and destroys the shackles.","grantedAtLevel":14,"infusion":{"active":false,"attuned":false,"choose":0,"desc":"Wondrous item, rare\n\nYou can use an action to place these shackles on an incapacitated creature. The shackles adjust to fit a creature of Small to Large size. In addition to serving as mundane manacles, the shackles prevent a creature bound by them from using any method of extradimensional movement, including teleportation or travel to a different plane of existence. They don\u0027t prevent the creature from passing-through an interdimensional portal.\n\nYou and any creature you designate when you use the shackles can use an action to remove them. Once every 30 days, the bound creature can make a DC 30 Strength (Athletics) check. On a success, the creature breaks free and destroys the shackles.","grantedAtLevel":14,"level":0,"name":"Dimensional Shackles"},"maxActive":{"static":0},"name":"Dimensional Shackles"},{"activationRequirement":{},"description":